            {"q": "What is a Neural Network?", "a": "A computational architecture inspired by human biological neural structures, consisting of interconnected layers of artificial nodes (neurons) that process data features."},
            {"q": "What is Deep Learning?", "a": "A specialized subfield of machine learning built around multi-layered artificial neural networks designed to automatically extract complex abstractions from massive raw datasets datasets."},
            {"q": "What is the purpose of an Activation Function in neural networks?", "a": "Activation functions introduce non-linear properties into neural network layers, allowing the network to learn and model complex, non-linear real-world relationships relationships."},
            {"q": "What is Natural Language Processing (NLP)?", "a": "A branch of AI focusing on the interaction between computers and human languages, enabling software to read, analyze, and generate human speech and text text."},
            {"q": "What is Computer Vision?", "a": "A field of AI enabling computer systems to capture, process, extract, and interpret meaningful features from digital images, video frames, and visual inputs inputs."}
