            {"q": "How do you safely expose database primary keys to frontend consumers without introducing security reconnaissance vulnerabilities?", "a": "Exposing auto-incremented database IDs allows attackers to guess records sequentially. To prevent this, full-stack systems should map entities to secure, random UUIDs for public API exposures, keeping native sequential IDs private internal tracking tracking metrics."},
            {"q": "Explain the process of tracing memory leak traces inside a Java production environment using automated heap dump triggers and Eclipse MAT analyzer.", "a": "JVM is started with -XX:+HeapDumpOnOutOfMemoryError flags flags. When crashes occur, the generated hprof binary is loaded into Eclipse MAT. Running the Leak Suspects report identifies dominant classloader chains and object arrays retaining unreferenced memory blocks blocks."},
