            {"q": "Explain how you handle optimistic lock exceptions within asynchronous retry loops using Spring Retry annotations.", "a": "Methods are decorated with @Retryable, specifying ObjectOptimisticLockingFailureException as the target filter, and configuring backoff delays delays. If updates collide, Spring automatically retries the operation, reloading the fresh database state before executing updates updates."},
            {"q": "Detail the system architecture requirements to support complete offline capabilities for a React progressive web app backed by a Java engine.", "a": "The frontend registers service workers to cache app shell bundles bundles, and utilizes IndexedDB to queue user data mutations locally offline. Upon reconnecting, background sync processes transmit queued updates to Spring Boot endpoints to resolve state conflicts conflicts."},
