            {"q": "How do you implement secure rate-limiting logic across a full-stack system using token bucket algorithms implemented inside Redis?", "a": "The backend evaluates client IP addresses or user keys keys against a Redis script. The script calculates token counts using a bucket capacity and a refresh rate. If tokens are available, the count decrements and the API proceeds; otherwise, it returns a 429 status status."},
            {"q": "Explain how to monitor enterprise full-stack application health traces using Prometheus metrics scraping and Grafana visualization dashboards.", "a": "Spring Boot apps include micrometer dependencies to expose internal metrics at /actuator/prometheus. A Prometheus server polls this endpoint periodically to collect statistics, and Grafana maps those metrics into real-time dashboards to monitor system health health trends."},
